---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'AXA Global in Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-axa', text: 'Why AXA for Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Who It\'s Best For', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Colombia', href: '/countries/colombia/insurance' },
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'AXA vs Allianz', href: '/compare/axa-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 35)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Essential', coverage: 'Core inpatient', price: '$110-150/mo' },
  { plan: 'Comfort', coverage: 'Inpatient + outpatient', price: '$150-200/mo' },
  { plan: 'Comprehensive', coverage: 'Full coverage', price: '$200-260/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="AXA Global Health Insurance in Colombia"
  description="Guide to AXA Global international health insurance for expats in Colombia. European insurance giant with comprehensive worldwide coverage."
  headline="AXA Global in Colombia"
  subheadline="European insurance powerhouse with strong global network. Reliable coverage for Colombia expats and digital nomads."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/colombia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an AXA Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/axa-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">AXA Global in Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    AXA is one of the world's largest insurance companies, and their international health division brings that scale and stability to expats in Colombia. For those who value the backing of a major European insurer, AXA provides reliable, comprehensive coverage.
  </p>
  <p>
    With a strong presence in Latin America and established relationships with Colombian healthcare providers, AXA is well-positioned to serve the Colombia expat market.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$150-260</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 35)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Global Giant</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Major insurer backing</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Strong in LATAM</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Latin America presence</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your AXA Colombia Quote"
    description="Comprehensive coverage from a global insurance leader."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/axa-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-axa">Why AXA for Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    AXA Global works well for Colombia expats for several reasons:
  </p>

  <h3>Financial Stability</h3>
  <p>
    As one of the world's largest insurers, AXA's financial strength provides confidence that claims will be paid. This matters for long-term coverage planning.
  </p>

  <h3>Latin America Expertise</h3>
  <p>
    AXA has significant operations throughout Latin America:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Understanding of regional healthcare systems</li>
    <li>Established hospital relationships in Colombia</li>
    <li>Spanish-language support available</li>
    <li>Experience with Latin American expat needs</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Hospital Network</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bogotá:</strong> Access to Fundación Santa Fe, major private hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Medellín:</strong> Coverage at leading facilities</li>
    <li><strong>Direct billing:</strong> Available at network hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Other cities:</strong> Cartagena, Cali, Barranquilla coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Flexible Plans</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Multiple coverage tiers</li>
    <li>Deductible options to control costs</li>
    <li>Optional add-ons for dental, vision</li>
    <li>Worldwide or regional coverage choices</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 35-year-old. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, selected coverage, and deductible.
  </p>

  <h3>Cost Factors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age:</strong> Primary driver of premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Plan level:</strong> Essential vs Comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage area:</strong> Americas-only vs worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible:</strong> Higher deductibles reduce premiums</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Including US adds to costs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, ICU, cancer treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, diagnostics (Comfort+)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation and repatriation</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Coverage included with limits</li>
    <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Covered after waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: Moratorium or underwriting</li>
    <li>Maternity: Waiting period, optional on some plans</li>
    <li>Dental/vision: Optional add-ons</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Who It's Best For</h2>

  <h3>European Expats</h3>
  <p>
    Those familiar with AXA from Europe appreciate the continuity. If you've had AXA coverage before, the experience will feel familiar.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-term Residents</h3>
  <p>
    AXA's financial stability and lifetime renewability make it suitable for expats planning to stay in Colombia for many years.
  </p>

  <h3>Corporate Expats</h3>
  <p>
    Companies often choose AXA for employee international health plans. If your employer offers AXA, it's a solid choice.
  </p>

  <h3>Those Valuing Stability</h3>
  <p>
    If the backing of a major global insurer matters to you—financial strength ratings, long operating history, scale—AXA delivers.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Visa Compliance</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      AXA Global meets Colombia's digital nomad visa insurance requirements. Policy documents serve as proof of coverage for visa applications.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare AXA Plans for Colombia"
    description="Find comprehensive coverage from a global leader."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/axa-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details are estimates based on typical scenarios. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your age, health, and coverage needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
